013    package net.sf.oval.internal.util;
014    
015    import static net.sf.oval.Validator.getCollectionFactory;
016    
017    import java.util.Collection;
018    import java.util.Iterator;
019    import java.util.List;
020    import java.util.ListIterator;
021    import java.util.Set;
022    
023    /**
024     *  @author Sebastian Thomschke
025     */
026    public class LinkedSet<E> implements Cloneable, Set<E>, List<E>
027    {
028            private final List<E> list;
029    
030            /**
031             * Constructs a new, empty collection with an initial capacity (16).
032             */
033            public LinkedSet()
034            {
035                    list = getCollectionFactory().createList(16);
036            }
037    
038            /**
039             * Constructs a new, empty collection with the given initial capacity.
040             *
041             * @param initialCapacity the initial capacity
042             */
043            public LinkedSet(final int initialCapacity)
044            {
045                    list = getCollectionFactory().createList(initialCapacity);
046            }
047    
048            /**
049             * {@inheritDoc}
050             */
051            public boolean add(final E e)
052            {
053                    return list.add(e);
054            }
055    
056            /**
057             * {@inheritDoc}
058             */
059            public void add(final int index, final E e)
060            {
061                    if (!list.contains(e))
062                    {
063                            list.add(index, e);
064                    }
065            }
066    
067            /**
068             * {@inheritDoc}
069             */
070            public boolean addAll(final Collection< ? extends E> c)
071            {
072                    boolean itemAdded = false;
073                    for (final E o : c)
074                    {
075                            if (!list.contains(o))
076                            {
077                                    add(o);
078                                    itemAdded = true;
079                            }
080                    }
081                    return itemAdded;
082            }
083    
084            /**
085             * {@inheritDoc}
086             */
087            public boolean addAll(final int index, final Collection< ? extends E> c)
088            {
089                    final List<E> tmp = getCollectionFactory().createList(c.size());
090                    for (final E o : c)
091                    {
092                            if (!list.contains(o))
093                            {
094                                    tmp.add(o);
095                            }
096                    }
097                    return list.addAll(index, tmp);
098            }
099    
100            /**
101             * {@inheritDoc}
102             */
103            public void clear()
104            {
105                    list.clear();
106            }
107    
108            /**
109             * {@inheritDoc}
110             */
111            @Override
112            public Object clone() throws CloneNotSupportedException
113            {
114                    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
115                    final LinkedSet<E> os = (LinkedSet<E>) super.clone();
116                    os.list.addAll(list);
117                    return os;
118            }
119    
120            /**
121             * {@inheritDoc}
122             */
123            public boolean contains(final Object o)
124            {
125                    return list.contains(o);
126            }
127    
128            /**
129             * {@inheritDoc}
130             */
131            public boolean containsAll(final Collection< ? > c)
132            {
133                    return list.containsAll(c);
134            }
135    
136            /**
137             * {@inheritDoc}
138             */
139            @Override
140            public boolean equals(final Object obj)
141            {
142                    if (this == obj) return true;
143                    if (obj == null) return false;
144                    if (getClass() != obj.getClass()) return false;
145                    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
146                    final LinkedSet other = (LinkedSet) obj;
147                    if (list == null)
148                    {
149                            if (other.list != null) return false;
150                    }
151                    else if (!list.equals(other.list)) return false;
152                    return true;
153            }
154    
155            /**
156             * {@inheritDoc}
157             */
158            public E get(final int index)
159            {
160                    return list.get(index);
161            }
162    
163            /**
164             * {@inheritDoc}
165             */
166            @Override
167            public int hashCode()
168            {
169                    final int prime = 31;
170                    int result = 1;
171                    result = prime * result + (list == null ? 0 : list.hashCode());
172                    return result;
173            }
174    
175            /**
176             * {@inheritDoc}
177             */
178            public int indexOf(final Object o)
179            {
180                    return list.indexOf(o);
181            }
182    
183            /**
184             * {@inheritDoc}
185             */
186            public boolean isEmpty()
187            {
188                    return list.isEmpty();
189            }
190    
191            /**
192             * {@inheritDoc}
193             */
194            public Iterator<E> iterator()
195            {
196                    return list.iterator();
197            }
198    
199            /**
200             * {@inheritDoc}
201             */
202            public int lastIndexOf(final Object o)
203            {
204                    return list.lastIndexOf(o);
205            }
206    
207            /**
208             * {@inheritDoc}
209             */
210            public ListIterator<E> listIterator()
211            {
212                    return list.listIterator();
213            }
214    
215            /**
216             * {@inheritDoc}
217             */
218            public ListIterator<E> listIterator(final int index)
219            {
220                    return list.listIterator(index);
221            }
222    
223            /**
224             * {@inheritDoc}
225             */
226            public E remove(final int index)
227            {
228                    return list.remove(index);
229            }
230    
231            /**
232             * {@inheritDoc}
233             */
234            public boolean remove(final Object o)
235            {
236                    return list.remove(o);
237            }
238    
239            /**
240             * {@inheritDoc}
241             */
242            public boolean removeAll(final Collection< ? > c)
243            {
244                    return list.removeAll(c);
245            }
246    
247            /**
248             * {@inheritDoc}
249             */
250            public boolean retainAll(final Collection< ? > c)
251            {
252                    return list.retainAll(c);
253            }
254    
255            /**
256             * {@inheritDoc}
257             */
258            public E set(final int index, final E element)
259            {
260                    final int elementIndex = list.indexOf(element);
261    
262                    if (elementIndex == index) return element;
263    
264                    if (elementIndex == -1) return list.set(index, element);
265                    if (elementIndex > index)
266                    {
267                            list.remove(element);
268                            return list.set(index, element);
269                    }
270    
271                    // if (elementIndex < index)
272                    list.remove(element);
273                    return list.set(index - 1, element);
274            }
275    
276            /**
277             * {@inheritDoc}
278             */
279            public int size()
280            {
281                    return list.size();
282            }
283    
284            /**
285             * {@inheritDoc}
286             */
287            public List<E> subList(final int fromIndex, final int toIndex)
288            {
289                    return list.subList(fromIndex, toIndex);
290            }
291    
292            /**
293             * {@inheritDoc}
294             */
295            public Object[] toArray()
296            {
297                    return list.toArray();
298            }
299    
300            /**
301             * {@inheritDoc}
302             */
303            public <T> T[] toArray(final T[] a)
304            {
305                    return list.toArray(a);
306            }
307    
308            /**
309             * {@inheritDoc}
310             */
311            @Override
312            public String toString()
313            {
314                    return list.toString();
315            }
316    }
